/td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=akethadar>Akethadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/2/03 9:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2138.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Everquest =(</span><hr size=1> As I write this, I'm leading a troop of courageous and dedicated adventurers through the lair of the evil mistress of Torment, Saryrn.  My tanks are taunting, my clerics are healing (except heallun.. he's talking), and my damage classes are doing damage.  Our goal?  The demise of another EQ deity! No wait... phat lewtz!! No wait... it's 7 flags that we need so that people can get into elemental planes without a raid.  And as I've sat here night after night this week, tearing into reflagging's like a bag of Doritos, I've had a lot of time to think about stuff (I recently moved into a new apartment and until Thursday, i was on dialup, which gives me 5 minutes to think about stuff everytime i hit a key, as i wait for the server to recieve my directions and return them to my screen).<br>
<br>
Everquest at one point was a game, all-be-it that it was more than your average game.  But it was a source of enjoyment, of excitement.  A few months ago there was a great quote on the frontpage of magister's site about why everquest, and specifically endgame everquest was so unique.. so enchanting ... so worth it.  It used to be that your raidguild would get together, and you would decide what you were killing that night, based on what was up and your own priorities, how you wanted to play the game.  There were choices.  Velious, the greatest of all EQ expansions presented guilds with so many options... 3 factions to choose from, be daring and go factionless (which was a bigger deal back before luclin than it is now in the world of 8k tanks in newb guilds), Sleeper's Tomb was the ultimate goal, and there were different ways to get there.  5 mobs dropped sleeper's keys, and you always had a choice of what you were going to kill.  A guild could advance to ST without ever killing Klandi, Zlandi, Yelinak, etc etc, as long as they killed some of the other key droppers.  When you raided, it was your time, and you.. or the officers you entrusted to make the decisions, got to decide which loot was best for your people, and which mobs you would go after (of course based on what was up).<br>
<br>
This changed somewhat in Luclin, but not until the very end.  You had to kill Emperor if you wanted in Vex Thal.  There were no 5 mobs to choose from, if you wanted to raid the land of the undead Akhevan Rock Robe Hell, you had to kill Emperor and advance that way.  No big deal, the rest of the expansion was open to interpretation.<br>
<br>
Now?  We sit here in the Plane of Torment not out of our own choice, not because I as a leader decided that Saryrn was hooray for my guild, but because I as a leader had no choice.  You raid linearly, progressively.  Every guild has to raid the same content.   If someone is missing a flag, and another guild has someone missing that same flag... only one of you is going to get it, PoP has encouraged cockblockage and inter-guild rivalry (not the point of racing to mobs, but the point of &quot;I hate those faggots that always kill Saryrn&quot;).<br>
<br>
Night after night i deal with 2 kinds of tells, depending on what we're doing.  Either &quot;Why do we have to reflag, we were here for the flags, we arent the slackasses that missed them.  we deserve loot mobs&quot; if we are doing reflaggings.... or &quot;I am sick of not being able to get into zones because of a missing flag, /bitch /moan /pissyourself&quot; because we are killing loot mobs.  Leaders of guilds that are not entirely hardcore (and i believe i'm safe in saying no hardcore guilds exist on vazaelle.  Even when Caer Cadarn was one of the top guilds in Everquest, it did so with a very laid back attitude) are constantly put in this situation.  Then we're put in the position of deciding whether we help flag our competition.<br>
<br>
Never before would another guild have had any reason to ask to raid with their competition except perhaps emp power sources.  There was no motivation for it.  Now, we have to firmly label who is our enemies and who are our friends.  Who do we cockblock, who do we assist in catching up or even possibly passing us?   Fuck this situation.  <br>
<br>
/bitching on.<br>
<br>
Promethian Order, prior to the release of Planes of Power, was 8 months ahead of its nearest competitor.  Caer Cadarn was 6 months ahead of us.  There was no question about who was numbre 1, and who was number 2.  We had followed Caer Cadarn through most of Luclin (because of a slow start because of Ammelen Le Velious =P /hug amm) and even at some points nipped at their heels (Hi serverfirst Shei Vinitras =D), but CC pulled far ahead after they locked Emp down.  And i mean locked it the fuck down.  Not that I can say i wouldnt have done the same thing in Baldrik's place, and we've talked about the situation afterwards.  It angered me, but was not something i couldnt understand.  At this point we had killed everything in luclin except emp, VT, Seru (but we were hacking at him, had him to 32 a week before pop release, and had emp to 60'ish before pop release on one of the 2 attempts we had at him).  Enter PoP.  EA had not even killed AoW at this point, and we were knocking on the door of the next expansion.   PoP adds 5 new levels, and erases fucking years of competitive edge in a matter of a month.<br>
<br>
It trivialized everything, including it's own early content, to the point that even a guild that had never touched Ssra temple could waltz in and knock on the doors of Elemental Planes.  But you had to do it in the order they prescribed.  Why was there such horrible itemization in PoP?  YOU HAD NO CHOICE.  You couldnt NOT kill the mob, they could have put cloth sandals on the mobs and you still would have had to go in and kill the mob, not once.. but over and over till you flag every last app on the last day before you enter plane of time.<br>
<br>
They finally made some encounters worth fighting, but then made them such horrible rvr that even intrepid adventurers and eq fans get sick of doing them over and over.  People ask me if leading raids for an endgame guild is like a job.  yes it is.  But being in the guild at all now is a job.  We have no options.  We kill what we HAVE to kill to progress.  No choices, no favorite encounters that we can do over and over.<br>
<br>
Elemental Planes are a joke.  And they're made that way on purpose because people spent the first 3 tiers bitching about itemization.  So hi overitemization.<br>
<br>
I'm depressed, I'm pissed.  I'm whining/ranting whatever.  But fuck this, I hate this shit.<br>
<br>
and fuck you Shadowpaa, you fucking loser.<br>
<br>
Ake<br>
<br>
PS - Saryrn without sorrowsong is fucking retarded too.  make him a pet spawn that spawns everytime she does.  The encounter's ghey and easy enough without this bullshit piece of shit broken crap happening so that even Eye of the Deciever could waltz in and kill her with no foreknowledge of the script. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1657<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/2/03 9:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2138.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Everquest =(</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Night after night i deal with 2 kinds of tells, depending on what we're doing. Either &quot;Why do we have to reflag, we were here for the flags, we arent the slackasses that missed them. we deserve loot mobs&quot; if we are doing reflaggings.... or &quot;I am sick of not being able to get into zones because of a missing flag, /bitch /moan /pissyourself&quot; because we are killing loot mobs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
