<br>
Velious was the best raiding zone in the game for sure. The triple choice of Tormax, Yeli, and Dain. Or heck, kill all three. Then you have the Temple of Veeshan, the single most fun raiding zone ever in EQ. Some decent exp zones but nothing like Kunark for pure fun.<br>
<br>
Kunark was the best dungeon expansion for single groups by far. Sebilis rocked. Karnors castle was quite cool if ya got into the zone and did not do the entrance. City of Mist was an awesome premise and a underrated exp zone if you went up into the upper parts. Chardok was also alot of fun when it first opened. Howling stones was cool. Back when this expansion was the newest thing in EQ all the loot that we think sucks now was totally cool and the good stuff was not easy to get. You get a MOSS you had to pay well for it or have a decent raid. You get a Noci Blade and you had to have a great group, good luck affording one. Great items were still a status symbol and something to be proud to have. There were no Windblade's for every newbie to pickup off the ground, no Centi Longswords dropping like flys. I remember how cool Kunark was when it first opened for a single group to explore. It was a decent raiding expansion as well with all the class specific stuff to go after, Trak and his BP's, Undead dood and his legs (been away too long, WTH was his name?), nice rare drops like a JBB, Cobalt bracer, and other nifty items that were a treat, dont forget that Fungi.<br>
<br>
Luclin was not a terrible raiding zone. As you said Ake people had a choice. Ssra gave you many options to kill in a single zone. Hitting up the Arch Lich, High Priest, Cursed, and creator was possible in a single raid and was pretty fun. The Deep gave you two mobs that were decent kills in the THO and Burrower, little too much plowing to get to them maybe but still not bad. Shei and Itraer in Akheva were decent, Shei was a cool encounter. The key quest for the emp and the key quest for Vex Thal were gimp. I spent days camping those bloody uber snakes at the emp zone for those signet things and a huge amount of time more camping shards and crap. Then you have bane weapons? Velious did not need these dumb time sinks, why did Luclin? I never even did get my Vex Thal key so who knows about that zone, I have read it is a hella amount of plowing which sounds pretty consistent for Luclin. Luclin also was the first expansion to really screw up the economy with mudflation of awesome items dropping like crazy and being droppable. Even no drop items were dropping so much people were just looting other peoples kills and getting unreal items.<br>
<br>
Then comes PoP. I quit EQ right about the time this came out because there was no way in hell I was going to go through an even bigger time sink then Luclin. I was just about done the luclin keys and crap and in all of a week I had fallen behind my guild in PoP. If you miss a raid you are teh scrood! Well being softcore at that point I said screw it and quit. After reading all the crap about PoP I cannot say I am sad. I made a post about the planes on the general disscussion. Not only is PoP screwed up by being linear it is also totally a screwy way to implement planes. Clicky entrances all in the same frickin zone? Hello lazy bloody writers and programmers! PoP is like surfing a frickin webpage with certain little tasks before you get into each next nifty page. Planes shoudl have been implemented into existing zones where they would make sense. Plane of underfoot in the Hole behind Yael, Plane of Disease in the hidden catacombs of Unrest under the basement or maybe on an extension of the zone where the spelunker was. Plane of Fire in Sol B in some new secret area. Plane of Ice (is there even one?) In Permafrost somehere. Heck even link Sol B and Permafrost with an underground maze of new content and have the entrances of those two planes somewhere in there, this is not rocket science and is hella more interesting. You get the idea. All the planes neatly packaged as they are is total crap. &quot;Welcome back to the homepage of Tranquility, click *HERE* for the Plane of Earth&quot;<br>
<br>
